        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 17 at 3:57AM CDT until August 17 at 4:15AM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 356 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Morocco to 6 miles south of Roselawn to near
DeMotte, moving southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Thayer, Sumava Resorts, Roselawn, Mount Ayr, Stoutsburg, Momence,
DeMotte, Fair Oaks, Hopkins Park, Parr, Schneider, Shelby, Lake
Village, and Rensselaer.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
